examples.en: The police searched the suspect
The area was thoroughly searched.
They searched him, but he was clean.
He was searched by the guard before he was allowed to enter the courtroom.
Anya searched his face anxiously.
We searched every nook and cranny.
He frantically searched for the key.
She searched the table for omissions.
She searched for information on the Web.
The premises were searched by the police.
He searched for treasure on the ocean bed
We searched hopefully for a good position.
They searched his luggage for illegal drugs.
They searched the room for hidden microphones.
Police searched in vain for the missing gunman.
We searched the whole house for the missing keys.
He searched through piles of letters and clippings.
searched for a priest who could perform an exorcism
He searched for a priest who could perform an exorcism.
He searched for information on his relatives on the web.
The police searched the length and breadth of the country.
He searched her face, hoping to see some glimmer of emotion.
They searched his pockets, and found all his copper was base.
Volunteers searched the area in the vain hope of finding clues.
The lawyer searched out the weaknesses in the witness's statement.
We searched the whole area but all to no avail. Robbie had disappeared.
I drifted all over the world, I searched everyplace. (D. Bowie, Be My Wife)
